comments:
Abolished 30.9.1897 to become the separate parishes of Appleby 
    Magna North and Appleby Magna South (both in Leicestershre).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Ashby de 
    la Zouch and Ashby Woulds.

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Coalville 
    and Ibstock. See also Table 2, note (i).

Transferred from Derbyshire to Leicestershire on 30.9.1897. See 
    also Table 2, notes (d) and (g).

On 30.9.1897 the part in Derbyshire was transferred to Leicestershire, so that thereafter 
    Oakthorpe & Donisthorpe was entirely in Leicestershire. See also Table 2, note (g).
Abolished 29.9.1894 to become the separate parishes of Overseal and Netherseal.

The part in Derbyshire was transferred to Leicestershire on 
    25.3.1884. See also Table 2, note (g).

Abolished 25.3.1884 and added to the parish of Ravenstone 
    with Snibstone.

Transferred from Derbyshire to Leicestershire on 30.9.1897. See 
    also Table 2, note (g).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Smisby.

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Coalville, 
    Coleorton, Swannington, Osgathorpe, Belton and Worthington. See also Table 
    2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Coalville 
    and Charley. See also Table 2, note (h).

Transferred from Derbyshire to Leicestershire on 30.9.1897. Abolished 
    1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Ashby de la Zouch, Oakthorpe & Donisthorpe and Measham.
